The paper discusses metric learning, which is a subfield of machine learning that deals with learning distance functions between data points. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). However, given that the paper focuses on generalization bounds and the performance of metric learning algorithms, cs.LG is the most likely sub-category. The other sub-categories are also relevant because metric learning is used in various applications such as image recognition, natural language processing, and social network analysis.
